result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Natasha Renee Whitefeather

records.addlTxt: Staff attorney contacted DOC. Matter resolved; no further action required.

Defendant Natasha Renee Whitefeather in court, in custody.  Attorney Colin Patrick McGinn in court for Natasha Renee Whitefeather.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Plea and Sentencing Hearing. State filed an amended information;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and projected to plead guilty.  Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Defense counsel and defendant confirms. 

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY to the amended information.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea. Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his/her rights.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements by State, Defense Counsel, and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:
Court ordered Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT to Case 22CF2651, with credit for 83 DAYS time served. Huber release to be determines by HOC staff and Day Reporting Center.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute sobriety.
- DNA sample.
- No possession of controlled substances/alcohol without a valid prescription.
- Random urine screens at least 1 time per month.
- No possession of firearms/ammunition/magazines/holsters/body armor. 
- Pursue full time/part time employment and/or education.
- No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

-Pay ALL MANDATORY costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including DNA)  during the term of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

20 day appeal rights given,
Court advised defendant of her right to seek postconviction relief.
